title: [Old Ta'Faendryl, Northwest]
description: A sunken spot beneath a cluster of apple trees has collected a considerable amount of moisture, turning the ground soft and wet.  Cricket chirps rise from the thick moss growing along the base of the tree roots.

A sunken spot beneath a cluster of apple trees has collected a considerable amount of moisture, turning the ground soft and wet.  Deep hoof prints and paw marks crisscross through the mud, uprooting the few strands of grass that have managed to sprout in this sun-starved area.
